<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-4459] CAMEL-4407 has caused a regression in the features.xml</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-4459</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>
&lt;p&gt;The scriptengine things that were added as part of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-4407&quot; title=&quot;camel-script feature should ship script implementation bundles like groovy/javascript/ruby&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CAMEL-4407&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CAMEL-4407&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; have made doing a features:install camel-script in a &quot;plain&quot; Karaf instance not work as those dependencies are not available in Central.   Thus, setups that worked in the past that did not need those no longer work.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Propose moving those three deps to a &quot;camel-script-optional&quot; feature that would not be pulled in by default.   If a user needs them, they would need to configure Karaf to pull from another repo.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
